{
  "name": "Field Medic",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/fleur-de-lis-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Skill </p><p>You are an able medic, allowing you to mend wounds quickly and get your allies back in the fight.</p><p> You gain the following benefits: </p><p>• Increase your Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>• You gain proficiency in Medicine.</p><p> If you are already proficient, you instead gain Mastery.</p><p>• You gain proficiency in Medicine Kits.</p><p> If you are already proficient, you instead gain Mastery.</p><p>• When you would beat the stabilization DC by 10 or more, the target creature also regains 1 hit point becoming conscious and you remove 1 death saving throw.</p><p> You can remove a death saving throw from a creature in this way twice per Full rest, per creature.</p><p>• As a bonus action, you can spend a use of your medicine kit.</p><p> If you do, you enhance the next Blood pill that you or another creature consumes.</p><p> When you do, they instead gain the maximum benefit of consuming one of these pills and do not need to roll.</p><p></p>",
